nt to understand the brain you\u2019re going to have to take a reductionist approach, one cell at a time.\u201d So Kandel studied the neural system of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sea_slug\" title=\"Sea slug\">sea slug<\/a> <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Aplysia_californica\" title=\"Aplysia californica\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Aplysia californica<\/a><\/i>, which has large nerve cells amenable to experimental manipulation and is a member of the simplest group of animals known to be capable of learning.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Eric_R._Kandel#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Kandel is a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Professor\" title=\"Professor\">professor<\/a> of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biochemistry\" title=\"Biochemistry\">biochemistry<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biophysics\" title=\"Biophysics\">biophysics<\/a> at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Columbia_University_College_of_Physicians_and_Surgeons\" title=\"Columbia University College of Physicians and Surgeons\">College of Physicians and Surgeons<\/a> at Columbia University. He is a Senior Investigator in the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Howard_Hughes_Medical_Institute\" title=\"Howard Hughes Medical Institute\">Howard Hughes Medical Institute<\/a>. He was also the founding director of the Center for Neurobiology and Behavior, which is now the Department of Neuroscience at Columbia University. Kandel's popularized account chronicling his life and research, <i>In Search of Memory: The Emergence of a New Science of Mind<\/i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-ISOM_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Eric_R._Kandel#cite_note-ISOM-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> was awarded the 2006 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Los_Angeles_Times_Book_Award\" title=\"Los Angeles Times Book Award\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Los Angeles Times Book Award<\/a> for Science and Technology.<\/p>","name":"Eric R. Kandel","place_of_birth":"Vienna ,  Austria","place_of_death":null,"text":"Eric R. Kandel ,  born in Austria , Physiology or Medicine, 2000","year":2000.0}